  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem">Why is thermal swimming at Tolantongo different?</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">Thermal swimming at Tolantongo does not take place in a man-made pool: it happens in natural limestone formations, inside caves with ceilings up to 15 meters high and in a river that flows through the interior of an 800-meter canyon. The constant 36°C temperature year-round allows you to enjoy bathing in any season.</p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">The thermal effect of 36°C water has documented relaxing properties: it dilates blood vessels, reduces muscle tension and generates a sustained feeling of well-being. The high mineral content of the water (carbonates, bicarbonates and sulfates) adds additional properties to the bathing experience.</p>
      <p>Unlike conventional spas that artificially heat water, at Tolantongo the heat is 100% geothermal: it comes from deep within the earth without any artificial intervention.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
